                    <h1>Classification of Vertebrates</h1>
                    <p>Vertebrates can be brocken down into the following five classes:
                        <ul style="margin-left: 25px;">
                            <li style="padding-top: 5px;">
                                <span style="color: yellowgreen;">Mammals: </span>Mammals are warm-blooded vertebrates that live on land. Mammals give birth to live babies and their young get nourishment from milk produced by their mothers. Mammals have
                                hairs. Exampls are humans, whales, elephants, rabits, rats, monkeys etc.
                            </li>
                            <li style="padding-top: 5px;">
                                <span style="color: yellowgreen;">Birds: </span>Birds are a type of warm-blooded vertebrates that are adapted to fly. Not all birds can fly but they all have wings. Birds lay eggs to reproduce. They have hollow bones and
                                their bodies are covered in feathers. Examples are chickens, penguins, pigeons, falcons, kites, parrots, hummingbirds etc.
                            </li>
                            <li style="padding-top: 5px;">
                                <span style="color: yellowgreen;">Reptiles: </span>Reptiles are cold-blooded vertebrates. Some reptiles live on land while some live in water or both. They lay eggs th reproduce. They breathe through lungs and their bodies
                                are covered in scales.
                            </li>
                            <li style="padding-top: 5px;">
                                <span style="color: yellowgreen;">Fishes: </span>Fishes are cold-blooded vertebrates that live in water. They have fins and breathe through their gills. Their bodies are covered in scales. Examples are sharks, eels, salmons,
                                seahorses etc
                            </li>
                            <li style="padding-top: 5px;">
                                <span style="color: yellowgreen;">Amphibians: </span>Amphibians are animals that need moist environment or water to survive. They are cold-blooded. They absorb water and breathe through their skin. Examples are frogs, toads,
                                salamanders etc.
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </p>
                </div>
