                    <p>A habitat is a place that an animal lives. It provides the animal with food, water and shelter. The two main types of habitat are Terrestrial or Land habitats and Aquatic or Water habitats.</p>
                    <p>Some examples of terrestrial habitats are forests, rainforests, deserts, grasslands, tundra, mountains etc.</p>
                    <p>Examples of aquatic habitats are fresh water and salt water. Fresh water include streams, rivers, swamps, lakes, ponds etc. While salt water include oceans, seas, salt lakes etc.</p>
                </div>
